  <title>Abel-Beth-Maacah (Maachah*)</title>
  <body>
<p class="h1">ABEL-BETH-MAACAH (MAACHAH*)</p>
<p class="fl">Alternate name for Abel, a fortified city in upper Galilee in <a href="?bref=1Kgs.15.20">1 Kings 15:20</a> and <a href="?bref=2Kgs.15.29">2 Kings 15:29</a>. It was also called Abel of Beth-Maacah (Maachah) in <a href="?bref=2Sam.20.14-15">2 Sm 20:14-15</a>. <span class="ital">See</span> <a href="?item=AbelPlace_Article_TyndaleOpenBibleDictionary">Abel (Place)</a>.</p>
